<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1749,1956]" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">
Thorax dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[429,574,1749,1775]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1643,1667]" captionTargetBox="[207,1357,841,1589]" captionTargetId="figure-54@10.[202,1385,801,1619]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 13. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Male. A. Wing; B- Thorax, lateral view; C. Scutum, scutellum and postscutellum, dorsal view; D. Mid, fore and hind legs (left to right), lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674069/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">Figs. 13B, C</figureCitation>
). Scutum with setae arising directly from surface, with lateral suture. Paratergite with one seta. Anepisternum well-developed, broadly bilobed posteriorly. Wing with patch of pigmentation in area of r-m and posterior to apex of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[589,597,1840,1854]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">3</subScript>
(
<figureCitation box="[611,717,1821,1847]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1643,1667]" captionTargetBox="[207,1357,841,1589]" captionTargetId="figure-54@10.[202,1385,801,1619]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 13. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Male. A. Wing; B- Thorax, lateral view; C. Scutum, scutellum and postscutellum, dorsal view; D. Mid, fore and hind legs (left to right), lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674069/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
); few macrotrichiae on membrane in apical portion of r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1355,1363,1840,1854]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">3</subScript>
; wing length 1.03–1.05 (1.04, n = 2) mm; CR 0.66–0.73 (0.71, n = 3). Halter pale. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[1117,1221,1857,1883]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1643,1667]" captionTargetBox="[207,1357,841,1589]" captionTargetId="figure-54@10.[202,1385,801,1619]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 13. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Male. A. Wing; B- Thorax, lateral view; C. Scutum, scutellum and postscutellum, dorsal view; D. Mid, fore and hind legs (left to right), lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674069/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="285">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
) yellowish brown, coxae, trochanter, and basal portion of femora lighter; hind tibial spur shorter than width of hind tibia, hind tibial comb with 9–10 spines. TRI 3.33 (n = 1), TRII 3.28 (n = 1), and TRIII 2.48 (n = 1); empodia present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">
Abdomen brown (
<figureCitation box="[408,513,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[393,1218,858,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-337@11.[340,1247,849,1771]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 14. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Male.A.Abdomen, ventral view; B.Aedeagal-parameral complex, ventral view; C-D. Terminalia, ventral view; E. Gonostylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674071/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
). Ventrolateral dark marks well developed on segments 1–3 and 5–8, smaller on segment 4. Terminalia dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[547,693,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[393,1218,858,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-337@11.[340,1247,849,1771]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 14. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Male.A.Abdomen, ventral view; B.Aedeagal-parameral complex, ventral view; C-D. Terminalia, ventral view; E. Gonostylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674071/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Figs. 14C, D</figureCitation>
), except for lighter gonostylus and cercus; sternite 9 with posterior margin nearly straight; tergite 9 moderately elongate, extending to the level of apex of gonocoxite. Gonocoxite without the medial lobe, gonocoxal apodeme greatly evident, triangular; length 2.00–2.27 (2.10, n = 3) × the basal width. Gonostylus pale brown, except of yellowish brown apical 1/2 (
<figureCitation box="[949,1052,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[393,1218,858,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-337@11.[340,1247,849,1771]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 14. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Male.A.Abdomen, ventral view; B.Aedeagal-parameral complex, ventral view; C-D. Terminalia, ventral view; E. Gonostylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674071/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 14E</figureCitation>
); swollen in basal half, with apex bifid with sclerotized inner claw. Aedeagal-parameral complex (
<figureCitation box="[889,992,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[393,1218,858,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-337@11.[340,1247,849,1771]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 14. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Male.A.Abdomen, ventral view; B.Aedeagal-parameral complex, ventral view; C-D. Terminalia, ventral view; E. Gonostylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674071/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
) nearly quadrangular, with short basal laterally directed arms, median portion trapezoidal, apical portion as a long pen feather connected with the median portion and gonocoxal apodeme of gonocoxite. Cercus yellowish brown, elongate, lobe-like, extending beyond the margin of tergite 9.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,475,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[303,408,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="12.[151,250,942,966]" captionTargetBox="[386,1235,236,858]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[324,1263,181,918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 15. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Female.A. Head, anterior view; B. Adult, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Maxillary palpus; E. Eyes separation, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674073/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 15B</figureCitation>
). Similar to male. Head (
<figureCitation box="[698,805,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="12.[151,250,942,966]" captionTargetBox="[386,1235,236,858]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[324,1263,181,918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 15. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Female.A. Head, anterior view; B. Adult, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Maxillary palpus; E. Eyes separation, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674073/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 15A</figureCitation>
); head width/mouthpart length 2.14–2.55 (2.33, n = 3). Eyes broadly abutting medially for length of 3.6–5.0. (4.26, n = 3) ommatidia (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1144,510,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="12.[151,250,942,966]" captionTargetBox="[386,1235,236,858]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[324,1263,181,918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 15. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Female.A. Head, anterior view; B. Adult, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Maxillary palpus; E. Eyes separation, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674073/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 15E</figureCitation>
). Antenna medium brown (
<figureCitation box="[160,261,546,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="12.[151,250,942,966]" captionTargetBox="[386,1235,236,858]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[324,1263,181,918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 15. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Female.A. Head, anterior view; B. Adult, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Maxillary palpus; E. Eyes separation, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674073/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 15C</figureCitation>
); flagellomeres 1–8 elongate, vasiform. AR 1.53–1.55 (n = 2). Mandibles with 23 teeth. Palpus (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1428,546,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="12.[151,250,942,966]" captionTargetBox="[386,1235,236,858]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[324,1263,181,918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 15. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Female.A. Head, anterior view; B. Adult, lateral view; C. Antenna; D. Maxillary palpus; E. Eyes separation, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674073/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 15D</figureCitation>
) light brown; third segment short to moderately elongated, pit at mid-length; segments 4 and 5 separated. PRIII 2.11–2.44 (2.25, n = 3). Thorax dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[672,777,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[307,1268,1039,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-54@12.[291,1296,1026,1942]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 16. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Female.A. Wing; B. Thorax posterolateral view; C. Hind, mid- and fore legs (left to right), lateral view; D. Spermatheca; E. Abdomen, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674075/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 16B</figureCitation>
). Wing pattern of pigmented membrane as for male (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[307,1268,1039,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-54@12.[291,1296,1026,1942]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 16. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Female.A. Wing; B. Thorax posterolateral view; C. Hind, mid- and fore legs (left to right), lateral view; D. Spermatheca; E. Abdomen, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674075/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
); macrotrichiae on membrane in apical portion of r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[775,783,673,687]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">3</subScript>
, m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[819,827,673,687]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">1</subScript>
, and apical half of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1069,1077,673,687]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">1</subScript>
; wing length 1.10–1.13 (1.11, n = 3) mm. CR 0.66–0.75 (0.69, n = 2). Legs as shown in figure 16C. Abdomen brown (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1222,691,718]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[307,1268,1039,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-54@12.[291,1296,1026,1942]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 16. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Female.A. Wing; B. Thorax posterolateral view; C. Hind, mid- and fore legs (left to right), lateral view; D. Spermatheca; E. Abdomen, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674075/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 16E</figureCitation>
), with lateral black marks; with ventrolateral dark marks well developed on segments 1–3, 5 and 8, smaller on segment 4; segments 8–10 brown. Genitalia. One medium brown, large, elliptic spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[960,1062,763,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[307,1268,1039,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-54@12.[291,1296,1026,1942]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 16. Atrichopogon sergioluzi sp. nov. Female.A. Wing; B. Thorax posterolateral view; C. Hind, mid- and fore legs (left to right), lateral view; D. Spermatheca; E. Abdomen, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4674075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4674075/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="286">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
), measuring 115 × 65 (n = 1) μm, with moderate neck 37.5 (n = 1) μm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
